#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.59"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.59:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 6. Upayavagga → pañcavaggiyasuttaṃ (bj) | pañca (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.59:0.2"
msgid "6. Upayavagga"
msgstr "6. Involvement"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.59:0.3"
msgid "59. Anattalakkhaṇasutta"
msgstr "59. The Characteristic of Not-Self"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Benares, in the deer park at "
"Isipatana."

msgctxt "sn22.59:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā pañcavaggiye bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the group of five mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn22.59:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpaṃ, bhikkhave, anattā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, form is not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.59:2.2"
msgid ""
"Rūpañca hidaṃ, bhikkhave, attā abhavissa, nayidaṃ rūpaṃ ābādhāya "
"saṃvatteyya, labbhetha ca rūpe:"
msgstr ""
"For if form were self, it wouldn’t lead to affliction. And you could compel "
"form:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:2.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘May my form be like this! May it not be like that!’"

msgctxt "sn22.59:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ anattā, tasmā rūpaṃ ābādhāya saṃvattati, na "
"ca labbhati rūpe:"
msgstr ""
"But because form is not-self, it leads to affliction. And you can’t compel "
"form:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:2.5"
msgid "‘evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘May my form be like this! May it not be like that!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.67"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:3.1"
msgid "Vedanā anattā."
msgstr "Feeling is not-self …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:3.2"
msgid ""
"Vedanā ca hidaṃ, bhikkhave, attā abhavissa, nayidaṃ vedanā ābādhāya "
"saṃvatteyya, labbhetha ca vedanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:3.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ me vedanā hotu, evaṃ me vedanā mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:3.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, vedanā anattā, tasmā vedanā ābādhāya saṃvattati, na "
"ca labbhati vedanāya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:3.5"
msgid "‘evaṃ me vedanā hotu, evaṃ me vedanā mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:4.1"
msgid "Saññā anattā … pe …"
msgstr "Perception is not-self …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:4.2"
msgid "saṅkhārā anattā."
msgstr "Choices are not-self …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:4.3"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhārā ca hidaṃ, bhikkhave, attā abhavissaṃsu, nayidaṃ saṅkhārā ābādhāya "
"saṃvatteyyuṃ, labbhetha ca saṅkhāresu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:4.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ me saṅkhārā hontu, evaṃ me saṅkhārā mā ahesun’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:4.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā anattā, tasmā saṅkhārā ābādhāya "
"saṃvattanti, na ca labbhati saṅkhāresu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.59:4.6"
msgid "‘evaṃ me saṅkhārā hontu, evaṃ me saṅkhārā mā ahesun’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:5.1"
msgid "Viññāṇaṃ anattā."
msgstr "Consciousness is not-self."

msgctxt "sn22.59:5.2"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇañca hidaṃ, bhikkhave, attā abhavissa, nayidaṃ viññāṇaṃ ābādhāya "
"saṃvatteyya, labbhetha ca viññāṇe:"
msgstr ""
"For if consciousness were self, it wouldn’t lead to affliction. And you "
"could compel consciousness:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:5.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ hotu, evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘May my consciousness be like this! May it not be like that!’"

msgctxt "sn22.59:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ anattā, tasmā viññāṇaṃ ābādhāya "
"saṃvattati, na ca labbhati viññāṇe:"
msgstr ""
"But because consciousness is not-self, it leads to affliction. And you can’t "
"compel consciousness:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:5.5"
msgid "‘evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ hotu, evaṃ me viññāṇaṃ mā ahosī’ti."
msgstr "‘May my consciousness be like this! May it not be like that!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.68"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:6.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.9"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling permanent or impermanent?” …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.10"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "“Is perception permanent or impermanent?” …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "“Are choices permanent or impermanent?” …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.14"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.15"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.16"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.17"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.59:6.18"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: "
"<em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not "
"this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yā kāci vedanā atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattā vā bahiddhā vā … pe … yā dūre "
"santike vā, sabbā vedanā: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "Any kind of feeling at all …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:9.1"
msgid "Yā kāci saññā … pe …"
msgstr "Any kind of perception at all …"

msgctxt "sn22.59:9.2"
msgid ""
"ye keci saṅkhārā atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā … pe … ye "
"dūre santike vā, sabbe saṅkhārā: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti "
"evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "Any kind of choices at all …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:10.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘"
"netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"You should truly see any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:11.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.59:11.2"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn22.59:11.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.59:12.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: abhinanduṃ → abhinandunti (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.59:12.2"
msgid "Attamanā pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanduṃ."
msgstr ""
"Satisfied, the group of five mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn22.59:12.3"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne pañcavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of the group of five "
"mendicants were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.59:12.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
